 Go to your settings, lock in,

261
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,040
 go to your settings,

262
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:24,340
 then go down to screen time.

263
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:31,080
 Then at screen time, go to see all app and website activity,

264
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:34,680
 and then scroll down a little,

265
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,840
 and you're gonna see this week with a blue arrow,

266
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,720
 click back to last week.

267
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,040
 (audience chattering)

268
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:46,080
 How many hours did you spend on your phone last week?

269
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:50,780
 The chatter is an indictment against you, okay?

270
00:13:50,780 --> 00:13:55,040
 Scroll down, scroll down.

271
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,920
 How many pickups did you have?

272
00:13:56,920 --> 00:14:04,000
 And then one more, scroll down.

273
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,480
 How many notifications did you have last week?

274
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,400
 All right, this is a safe place.

275
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:14,720
 How many of you were over six hours

276
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:15,880
 of screen time last week?

277
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:19,480
 Come on, safe place, safe place, safe place.

278
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,880
 God knows if you're lying.

279
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:24,240
 All right, put your hands down.

280
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,720
 Now put your phones away.

281
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,160
 Please put your phones away.

282
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,520
 We're in an anxiety message.

283
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,620
 Put those things away.

284
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:35,440
 All right, lock in, here's the reality.

285
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:38,640
 I know, you're judging your friends,

286
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,680
 you're either thinking you're awesome or you're terrible.

287
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:44,640
 Here's the reality, six to eight hours,

288
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:48,160
 guys, that is close to a full-time job

289
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,800
 that we are sucked into our phones.

290
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,800
 And this is not a message about phones, a technology.

291
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:55,960
 Here's what all this is trying to do.

292
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,920
 Jonathan Haidt calls your generation.

293
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:03,920
 He labels you, three simple words, the anxious generation.

294
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:08,760
 And some of us hear that and go, no, not me.

295
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:13,560
 And then you look at what's fueling you and you go, maybe.

296
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:16,960
 And not only your phones and not only social media,

297
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:20,600
 but over lunch, we had young adults,

298
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:24,720
 the thousand people who were there write cards anonymously

299
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,240
 of what's the hardest thing you've gone through

300
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:29,080
 over the past year and what's something you need to confess.

301
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,120
 Just every week, I've been reading some of those cards

302
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:33,160
 and in preparation for this sermon,

303
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:36,760
 I just read a couple and here was some of the cards

304
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,680
 that I read.

305
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:41,640
 One said, I struggle with anxiety

306
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:44,400
 and I'm a severe overthinker.

307
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:48,240
 I struggle with daily thoughts and memories

308
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:50,560
 and nightmares from trauma in my past.

309
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,600
 I cannot help, but think about it.

310
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:57,120
 Another one said, I am so scared to be alone.

311
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:59,360
 Nobody knows how I feel.

312
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:03,880
 I hate myself, I hate my body, I hate my face,

313
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,760
 I hate my personality.

314
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:08,560
 I compare myself to everyone else.

315
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:12,080
 I am so insecure and I don't trust God

316
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,680
 to let him take over my life.

317
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:17,920
 Another one said, I have deep crippling anxiety

318
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,120
 from college.

319
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:22,720
 I feel inadequate and I feel like I'm not enough.

320
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:26,080
 And then one more said, I am so anxious.

321
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:30,760
 I feel unloved, I feel unlovable, fearful.

322
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,160
 I can't do this anymore.

323
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:35,560
 This wasn't all the cards that I picked for.

324
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:36,520
 This was a little stack.

325
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:39,120
 I'm going, let me look if there's any with anxiety.

326
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:43,800
 And I think if we were honest, like gut level honest,

327
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:46,100
 many of you in this room feel a lot like that.

328
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:51,880
 Put on the face, sing the songs, have the meet and greet,

329
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,480
 but deep down we feel like that.

330
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,000
 I remember a few years ago, I was a pastor down in Houston

331
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,280
 and we were going through a series

332
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,440
 of kind of hot button things.

333
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:06,460
 And I was given the topic of sexuality

334
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:08,640
 and gender to preach on.

335
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:10,120
 It was my first time preaching on this.

336
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:14,040
 And I was so nervous, not because I was afraid

337
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:16,400
 of saying the truth, but because I had a lot of friends

338
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,500
 who I knew I'm gonna say the truth,

339
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,720
 this is gonna be really hard.

340
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,200
 And yet God, I wanna be faithful to you,

341
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,200
 but I wanna be loving.

342
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,120
 And I remember weeks, I'm prepping, prepping, prepping.

343
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:29,160
 And finally, Saturday night, I finished prepping.

344
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:32,600
 I go to sleep, I lay my head on the pillow

345
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,800
 and I can't fall asleep.

346
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:37,340
 And just my mind is racing, my heart is going.

347
00:17:37,340 --> 00:17:41,320
 I'm like, ah, and then one hour turned to two hours,

348
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:42,640
 two hours turned to three hours.

349
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,360
 I mean, I'm about to preach the next morning

350
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:47,880
 and I cannot get my mind to stop.

351
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:52,640
 Three hours, four, five, six, seven, zero minutes of sleep.

352
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:54,680
 Zero, have you had that?

353
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,560
 It's an all nighter that I didn't want, right?

354
00:17:57,560 --> 00:18:00,920
 And I wake up, I wake up, I get up the next morning

355
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:04,160
 and I go to church and deliver that sermon and praise God.

356
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,440
 Like it went well, it was good.

357
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,560
 I'm like, oh, thank you.

358
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,520
 Take a nap for like 20 years, you know?

359
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:13,420
 And then the next week I'm giving another sermon

360
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,280
 on something totally different.

361
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,460
 Not a hard topic, an easy one.

362
00:18:17,460 --> 00:18:21,160
 I lay my head on the pillow Saturday night

363
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:24,120
 and I had the thought, man, I hope I can fall asleep.

364
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:27,640
 And then one hour turned to two hours,

365
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,800
 turned to three hours.

366
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,120
 I only got two hours of sleep that night.

367
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:33,480
 I'm like, what is going on?

368
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:37,320
 Guys, for a year, every Saturday night,

369
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:40,260
 before I would teach, I could not sleep.

370
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:44,200
 I was going mad because I wasn't even,

371
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,400
 I wasn't even nervous.

372
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,080
 I was just had the thought of like,

373
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,800
 I hope I can fall asleep and I'm taking melatonin

374
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,880
 and I'm changing rooms and I'm listening

375
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:54,280
 to Shane and Shane music and I'm doing everything

376
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,440
 to try to put me to sleep.

377
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:59,600
 Nothing is working and I'm just so frustrated

378
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:03,680
 until finally after a year, guys, last night,

379
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:07,160
 last night, so I'm writing this message.

380
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,740
 I lay my head on the pillow and go, man,

381
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:11,940
 I remember when I couldn't fall asleep before a message.

382
00:19:11,940 --> 00:19:15,740
 Then one hour turned to two hours, turned to three.

383
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:18,760
 I'm like, no, that was younger me.

384
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:21,320
 Like I'm free of this.

385
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:25,100
 And I just like, oh, and all those anxious thoughts.

386
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:28,200
 I mean, I'm about to preach on anxiety

387
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:32,440
 as I spent a night last night living in anxious thoughts.

388
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:37,200
 My God, this is, I'm coming to you fellow struggler.

389
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:42,600
 Man, we need God's word, not some person to tell us

390
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:45,820
 how in the world do we make it through this.

391
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,740
 And that's why we're in Psalm 46.

392
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:54,560
 Psalm 46 is written by this group of worship leaders

393
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,740
 called the sons of Korah.

394
00:19:56,740 --> 00:20:00,360
 And most scholars believe Psalm 46 was written

395
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:04,600
 in the midst of national crisis in Judah.

396
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:08,320
 So the Assyrian army was coming against them.

397
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:11,400
 And as they were, they kind of look up one day

398
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:16,040
 and 185,000 Assyrian troops are surrounding them.

399
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:19,460
 And Hezekiah, the king of Israel looks out

400
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:22,080
 and he just cries out, God help us.

401
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:23,760
 He literally gets in front of everyone and just says,

402
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,720
 God, we need your help.

403
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,080
 Help us just like you did in the past, help us.

404
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,600
 And God sends one angel

405
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:34,640
 and overnight kills 185,000 Assyrian troops.

406
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:38,560
 And they wake up in the morning to see God won the battle

407
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,960
 without a single arrow being shot.

408
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:44,200
 And so these worship leaders are walking

409
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:47,880
 through this battle that God fought on their behalf.

410
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,960
 And they write Psalm 46.

411
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:54,000
 To infuse courage into the heart of the anxious.

412
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,040
 And it's so interesting what they write.

413
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:59,800
 And as we look at this, we're actually gonna see

414
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:04,200
 three ways to fight anxiety from Psalm 46.

415
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,440
 I wanna say this, Kylan said this last week.

416
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,720
 I wanna reiterate.

417
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,880
 We're not coming at this from a clinical perspective,

418
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:11,840
 from a doctor perspective.

419
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,120
 Some of you, there is neurons

420
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,440
 and there's things in your brain that it doesn't matter

421
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:19,320
 what kind of advice you get from a church or anywhere,

422
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,240
 you need extra help.

423
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:23,040
 And so this is not coming to heap.

424
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,040
 You better do these things

425
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:25,960
 and you won't be anxious anymore, no.

426
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:28,520
 In fact, I promise you that's not the case

427
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:30,140
 for anybody in this sermon.

428
00:21:30,140 --> 00:21:33,120
 What this is, is an invitation to look at God

429
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:37,320
 who created your mind and say, God, what do you want?

430
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:40,240
 And he lovingly begins to teach us

431
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,400
 how to fight things like anxiety.

432
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:46,860
 So Psalm 46, let's look at starting in verse one.

433
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:50,880
 It says, "God is our refuge and strength,

434
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:54,000
 "a very present help in trouble.

435
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:57,920
 "Therefore we will not fear, though the earth gives way,

436
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:00,940
 "though the mountains be moved into the heart of the sea,

437
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:03,500
 "though its waters roar and foam,

438
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,520
 "though the mountains tremble at its swelling."

439
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,360
 So how do you fight?

440
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,180
 Well, stop there.

441
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:10,380
 How do you fight anxiety from Psalm 46?

442
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:14,500
 The first thing is be honest about what's shaking you.

443
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,260
 Be honest about what's shaking you.

444
00:22:17,260 --> 00:22:20,180
 Did you catch what he said in verse one?

445
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:23,100
 He said, "God is our refuge and he's our strength,

446
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,660
 "a very present help in trouble."

447
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:29,700
 Not to fight trouble, not to cure trouble,

448
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:31,380
 in the midst of it.

449
00:22:31,380 --> 00:22:33,740
 He says, "Then, therefore I'm not gonna fear."

450
00:22:33,740 --> 00:22:36,220
 And then he gives four, those statements.

451
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:37,460
 He says, "Though the earth gives way,

452
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:38,720
 "though the mountains be moved,

453
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,340
 "though the waters roar and foam,

454
00:22:40,340 --> 00:22:41,540
 "though the mountains tremble."

455
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:42,380
 What are they saying?

456
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:44,420
 They said, "God, we trust your presence,

457
00:22:44,420 --> 00:22:47,980
 "but if we're honest, our world is pretty shaky right now."

458
00:22:47,980 --> 00:22:51,340
 They are real about what's going on.

459
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:54,120
 They don't pretend that everything's fine.

460
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:58,580
 I remember a few years ago, a buddy of mine,

461
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:01,500
 he was just going through a really rough time.

462
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:05,020
 Work was, his work was, his job was on the line.

463
00:23:05,020 --> 00:23:06,800
 He thought maybe he was gonna get fired.

464
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,460
 His kids, he had four kids, they're all sick.

465
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:11,980
 And then a waterline bursts in his house

466
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:13,580
 and his house is getting flooded.

467
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:17,060
 And so I text him, I'm like, "Hey man, how are you doing?"

468
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:19,140
 And he just texted me back this picture.

469
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,140
 You ever seen this?

470
00:23:20,140 --> 00:23:24,580
 And I love it, you know,

471
00:23:24,580 --> 00:23:26,020
 because he's obviously making fun of it.

472
00:23:26,020 --> 00:23:28,020
 But I just think of this picture for a second.

473
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:31,420
 How many of you, is this your life right now, right?

474
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:33,300
 And so Monday morning comes,

475
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,420
 we go, "Oh, how was the weekend?

476
00:23:34,420 --> 00:23:35,260
 "How are you doing?"

477
00:23:35,260 --> 00:23:36,100
 "Fine."

478
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:36,920
 "Right."

479
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,000
 "You have meet and greet time?"

480
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,320
 "Oh, how's life right now?"

481
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,360
 "It's fine."

482
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,200
 "Right."

483
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,540
 "Your boss, your small group?"

484
00:23:42,540 --> 00:23:43,760
 "Fine, fine."

485
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,040
 I used to tell, when I was a youth pastor,

486
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:48,720
 I used to tell students, you know what fine stands for?

487
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:50,680
 Feelings I'm not expressing.

488
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:52,880
 Fine, that's what fine is.

489
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:55,240
 And what are they saying here?

490
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:59,440
 Look, we're gonna be honest that our life is not fine.

491
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:00,800
 And I'm curious for you,

492
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:04,800
 where is your life shaking right now?

493
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:07,200
 You know, where are you not fine?

494
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:09,680
 And sometimes in church, we like that.

495
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,820
 So we just vent, "Oh, here's all the problems."

496
00:24:11,820 --> 00:24:14,220
 But that's not necessarily what's happening here.

497
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:17,300
 The sons of Korah in the Psalms are trying to identify

498
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:20,060
 what is fueling my fear.

499
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:24,460
 When we feel anxious, so often the thing

500
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:29,460
 that's fueling our anxiety feels so stupid and silly

501
00:24:29,460 --> 00:24:32,460
 and dumb that we never tell anybody

502
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:34,500
 because it feels like if I tell you this,

503
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:37,940
 you're gonna look down on me because it's so silly.

504
00:24:37,940 --> 00:24:40,020
 It's so irrational.

505
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:43,700
 And yet look at what, did you see what they said

506
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:47,700
 is causing them to tremble, is causing them to be scared?

507
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:51,580
 They said that mountains would be moved into the sea.

508
00:24:51,580 --> 00:24:52,540
 They're like, "We're not gonna fear,

509
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:54,620
 even though I don't know if that mountain's

510
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:55,940
 gonna be moved into the sea."

511
00:24:55,940 --> 00:24:58,900
 They're like speaking in this hyperbole kind of way

512
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,900
 of just this ridiculous scenario,

513
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,900
 but they're going, "In my mind, that's what it feels like.

514
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:05,020
 It feels like the whole world is falling

515
00:25:05,020 --> 00:25:07,580
 and mountains are falling into the sea."

516
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:08,940
 And they're honest.

517
00:25:08,940 --> 00:25:13,100
 They're honest about it and they express it to God

518
00:25:13,100 --> 00:25:14,340
 because he can handle it.

519
00:25:14,340 --> 00:25:18,060
 I love what Kylan said last week about prayer.

