00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:54,400
 that I've done in my life that have helped me in anxiety.

698
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,780
 I'm not saying they're the cure.

699
00:32:55,780 --> 00:32:57,160
 I'm not saying it solves everything.

700
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,320
 I'm just saying it's helped me.

701
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:02,160
 The first is in the midst of those anxious thoughts,

702
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:04,880
 you remember what God has done for you.

703
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:06,520
 You remember what God has done for you.

704
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:08,280
 And here's why.

705
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:11,060
 Did you know that scientists have studied the brain?

706
00:33:11,060 --> 00:33:12,720
 This is data, not Christians.

707
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:14,320
 They've studied the brain

708
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:19,200
 and they saw that when the brain is experiencing gratitude,

709
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:21,960
 that the frontal lobe begins to light up

710
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:23,600
 where your emotions are

711
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:26,640
 and your heart rate begins to slow down

712
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:30,880
 and your amygdala where your fear goes out

713
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:34,280
 begins to weaken its effect on the rest of your brain.

714
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:37,080
 That when you're experiencing gratitude,

715
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,280
 anxiety begins to fade.

716
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:41,600
 And I saw this last night.

717
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:44,960
 So last night, oh, I hope I can, hope I can fall asleep.

718
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,920
 Hour one, hour two, hour three, I'm sitting there.

719
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,360
 I'm mad guys.

